Heat grill. Cook and drain noodles as package directs except - reserve soup seasoning. Rinse noodles with cold water. Mix oil, vinegar, cilantro and 1 teaspoon soup seasoning. Toss noodles, onions, tomato and cucumber with dressing. Refrigerate until ready to serve. Rub each steak with 1 teaspoon seasoning. (Discard any remaining seasoning.) Place steaks on grill. Cover and cook over medium-high heat 8 to 12 minutes, turning once, for medium rare or to desired doneness. Thinly slice steaks and arrange over noodle salad.